description:
America's Deadliest



Aired on 02/25/2013, Narrated by: Jonathan Aris



On 25 May 1979, the left engine of American Airlines Flight 191, a McDonnell-Douglas DC-10-10, falls off moments after take-off at Chicago's O'Hare International Airport. The aircraft crashes into an open field shortly thereafter, killing all 271 people on board as well as two others on the ground.
